crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sample of the Abyss Locker V2 ransomware, specifically designed to target Linux systems and VMware ESXi environments. It demonstrates classic ransomware behavior by recursively traversing the filesystem (sub_404321), encrypting files using multi-threading and hardware-accelerated AES-NI instructions (sub_40689a, sub_40a8d0), and appending a '.crypt' extension. A ransom note named '.README_TO_RESTORE' is dropped (sub_405fd1), which contains an extortion message and a Tor onion link (jwqpucwiolhmivnqt7qwroezymksxfjsbj6pmg2lnnglqpoe26cwnryd[.]onion). Critically, the malware uses 'esxcli' commands ('esxcli vm process list', 'esxcli vm process kill') to identify and shut down running virtual machines, ensuring their disk files are accessible for encryption. It also includes capabilities to run as a daemon and logs its progress to 'work.log'.
